It was in Naples where Emma captured the heart of Lord Horatio Nelson, who began a curious ménage à trois with Lord and Lady Hamilton. All three visited Warwick and Warwick Castle in September 1802, with the bells of @StMarysWarwick rung out to greet them. (4/5) https://t.co/LVoqKu30MQ

Faced with debts and the inability to fund a mistress, Greville eventually sent Emma off to Naples and to his 56 year old uncle Sir William Hamilton in 1786. Companionship turned into love, and they married in 1791. (3/5) https://t.co/gDrWABEYMQ

It was Charles Francis Greville, younger brother to the Earl of Warwick, who took in Emma as his mistress in 1781. His connections to the London art world brought her into contact with leading painters who would immortalise her, including Reynolds and Romney. (2/5) https://t.co/dgAj1EqyR0

I failed to mention at the beginning to line a baking sheet with aluminum foil to set your pie shell on and assemble your quiche.  It will catch all the extra filling that oozes out.  Happy eating!
Then serve it up!  Here, with homemade applesauce, candied yams, and green bean casserole.  So good! https://t.co/RMvQSKap09

Slowly pour the egg mixture over and into the quiche.  Then into a 350F. oven for 45-60 minutes, till egg is set and cheese has melted.  Yes, it will ooze some off the sides and onto the foil.  Not a problem.  Take out of oven when done & let sit a few minutes to firm things up. https://t.co/kB72tosTWz

Add more Swiss cheese, then decorate the top with sliced fresh tomato.  Sprinkle with parmesan and parsley flakes. https://t.co/l1yzCP1rZF

We're going to be adding canned artichoke hearts, too. https://t.co/hqfGwYGETH
Let's add some more cheese.  I have Italian blend and more cheddar. https://t.co/Gh19LfxdgW
